4) The species most closely related to the Flying Fox (Pteropus lylei) are Syconycteris australis and Dobsonia viridis. The next closest relatives seem to be Cynopterus sphinx and Rousettus leschenaultii, all within the Pteropodidae family.

5) ACE2 is the receptor SARS-CoV-2 uses to enter human cells. Bats are a known reservoir host for coronaviruses, so understanding which bat species have ACE2 sequences most similar to humans helps identify potential intermediate hosts for future spillover events, which is critical for pandemic preparedness.